@ljharb I developed a class to create cron tasks in JavaScript. By default the task function is called with the class instance for `this`. But the user can define another `this`.

Here is a simplified version of my class:

```JavaScript
export const Cron = class {

    #cronex;
    #func;
    #thisArg = this;
    #args = [];

    constructor(cronex, func) {
        this.#cronex = cronex;
        this.#func = func;
    }

    bind(thisArg, ...args) {
        this.#thisArg = thisArg;
        this.#args = args;
    }

    run() {
        this.#func.bind(this.#thisArg)(...this.#args);
    }

    // ...
};
```

And the full version in [cronnor](https://github.com/regseb/cronnor/blob/v1.3.0/src/cron.js#L46).
